Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView selection):

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** — both arrive in the same method:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using ProductId...
        }

        // Approach B — full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** on the page:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <!-- BindingContext set via DI or code-behind -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?key=val`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | Strings only | Any object |
| **Serialization** | URL-encoded | Passed by reference |
| **Back-nav safe** | ✅ survives stack rebuild | ❌ object may be lost on pop |
| **Best for** | IDs, simple values | Complex objects already in memory |

> **Tip:** Always `await` `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions. Use `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` when you already have the object loaded and want to avoid a redundant fetch on the target page.
